title: Printer's Sample Book, Book 3 1887, 1886–88
medium: leather, paper, and printed cotton textile samples
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small dark brown leather-bound book with textiles samples. Natural and synthetic dyes. Mostly small-patterned geometric and floral prints on plain weave cotton. 148 samples.
